it.polimi.constraints.components

Class Replacement

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.polimi.constraints.components.Component
      • it.polimi.constraints.components.Replacement

  • public class Replacement
extends Component
    The Replacement class extends the Component class and specifies the IBA which represent the model that describes the replacement of the black box state.
    Author:
    Claudio Menghi

      • Replacement

        public Replacement(State modelState,
                   IBA automaton,
                   Set<PluggingTransition> incomingTransitions,
                   Set<PluggingTransition> outcomingTransitions)
        creates a new sub-property that refers to a specific model state and contains the corresponding IBA
        Parameters:
        modelState - is the state of the model to which the sub-property corresponds with
        automaton - is the automaton related with the sub-property
        incomingTransitions - the incoming transitions of the replacement
        outcomingTransitions - the outgoing transitions of the replacement
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - is generated when the name of the state or when the state of the model is null

      • getOutgoingTransitions

        public Collection<PluggingTransition> getOutgoingTransitions(State modelState,
                                                             State destinationState,
                                                             Set<rwth.i2.ltl2ba4j.model.IGraphProposition> propositions)
        returns the collection of outgoing transitions which have as source the model state. If no outgoing transitions are associated with the model state an empty collection is returned
        Parameters:
        modelState - the state of the replacement from which the outgoing transitions are fired
        destinationState - the destination of the outgoing transitions to be returned
        propositions - the propositions that label the outgoing transitions
        Returns:
        the collection of the outgoing transitions which have the modelState as source state
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the model state is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the model state is not a state of the replacement automaton

      • getIncomingTransitions

        public Collection<PluggingTransition> getIncomingTransitions(State modelState,
                                                             Set<rwth.i2.ltl2ba4j.model.IGraphProposition> propositions)
        returns the collection of incoming transitions with the specified modelState, destinationState and propositions. If no incoming transitions are associated with the modelState, destinationState and the set of propositions an empty collection is returned
        Parameters:
        modelState - the state of the model which is the source from which the incoming transitions is fired
        propositions - the set of propositions that label the incoming transition
        Returns:
        the collection of the incoming transitions which have the specifiedmodelState, destinationState and the set of propositions
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the model state is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the model state is not a state of the replacement automaton

      • hasIncomingTransition

        public boolean hasIncomingTransition(State modelState,
                                     Set<rwth.i2.ltl2ba4j.model.IGraphProposition> propositions)
        returns the true if there is an incoming transition of the replacement which has the specified destination state and is labeled with the specified propositions
        Parameters:
        modelState - the state of the model which is the source of the incoming transition
        propositions - the propositions that label the replacement
        Returns:
        true if there is whose destination is the specified state and the transition is labeled according to the propositions specified as parameter
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the model state is null
        IllegalArgumentException - if the model state is not a state of the replacement automaton
